This paper deals with the problem of inferring neuronal connectivity patterns from multi-neuronal spike train data, which involves finding significant temporal patterns from vast amounts of symbolic time series data. This problem is highly relevant to the fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence, as well as to the study of neural systems. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
